If the current targets are reached, it means a growth rate of 12 to 17 percent compared to the record profit of $290,4 million during the period 2011/12.
Managing Director Graham Turner announced that flight Centre scored eight percent gain in the first half of the year and reported a strong start in the second half of the year, especially in the Australian and British private business.
"Since the beginning of the year, our ten countries are profitable and some of them are well on the way toward record annual revenues before interest and taxes," he said.
These include Australia and the United Kingdom, that typically belong to our strongest sources of earnings.
